Stopped into the Dunkin’ today and I must say, this place is terrible. I can’t believe they are still in business. I mean, I can’t believe they have customers who buy food and drink from this place.  Today on my visit I ordered an iced latte and two donuts. The iced latte was not bad, but the donuts were stale. I asked for fresher ones and guess what I was handed?... You guessed it, more stale ones. For the iced latte, I originally awarded 2 Stars for this review (I couldn’t give more on account of the horrible cleanliness and homeless people occupying the store). However, I snatch that 1 star right on back because of the crusty, hard donuts I was given twice.  Years ago when I would visit this place, it was very nice. Awesome place to come catch some WiFi and a coffee. I used to enjoy seating at the upper level. Now even that is closed. Sad to see her go 👋.  In closing, this one is to the leadership and people of the city of DC: What do you guys plan to do about the mental, homeless people who are at every corner & at every establishment asking for people’s change? We have to do better. It’s gross.

I understand the negative reviews, and at times it is hard to understand some of the servers - but today's experience redeemed that in my eyes.  Yesterday, I was accidentally charged for someone else's order - since it was on my phone and took a little while to update I didn't realize until I had already left. Today, I didn't even have to mention the screw up - the server told me and gave me a full refund. They didn't even charge me for my drink.  I have found this Dunkin Donuts quite reliable for coffee and iced tea, which is what I always get - and good for the occasional wake-up wrap. While I cannot always understand the staff, they have been very nice, especially in light of this mistaken charge.
